  16:..\..\FreeflyAPI/QX_Protocol.c **** 	Filename: "QX_Protocol.c"
  17:..\..\FreeflyAPI/QX_Protocol.c **** 
  18:..\..\FreeflyAPI/QX_Protocol.c **** 	Description: This file provides the non-project specific portions of the Freefly QX Protocol
  19:..\..\FreeflyAPI/QX_Protocol.c **** 
  20:..\..\FreeflyAPI/QX_Protocol.c **** 	Reuse and Porting:
  21:..\..\FreeflyAPI/QX_Protocol.c **** 	This code is design for simple reuse in other projects
  22:..\..\FreeflyAPI/QX_Protocol.c **** 	by separation of the protocol code/data from the application code/data.
  23:..\..\FreeflyAPI/QX_Protocol.c **** 	Steps:
  24:..\..\FreeflyAPI/QX_Protocol.c **** 	1.	Include QX_Protocol.c/.h and QX_Parsing_Util.c/.h files in your new project. 
  25:..\..\FreeflyAPI/QX_Protocol.c **** 		These should not be modified for the application.
  26:..\..\FreeflyAPI/QX_Protocol.c **** 	2.	Write the QX_Protocol_App.c/.h files. Other projects can be used as a template.
  27:..\..\FreeflyAPI/QX_Protocol.c **** 		This contains the client/server parser callback functions, support functions, 
  28:..\..\FreeflyAPI/QX_Protocol.c **** 		and QX_SendMsg2CommsPort_CB() which should send the messages to the desired port.
  29:..\..\FreeflyAPI/QX_Protocol.c **** 		The message support arrays (QX_Cli_MsgSupport and QX_Srv_MsgSupport)
  30:..\..\FreeflyAPI/QX_Protocol.c **** 		should also be initialized with the supported messages and their length check enforcement status.
ARM GAS  C:\Users\hamis\AppData\Local\Temp\ccsOK97v.s 			page 2


  31:..\..\FreeflyAPI/QX_Protocol.c **** 	3. Define the number of servers and clients in your system by defining QX_NUM_SRV and QX_NUM_CLI i
  32:..\..\FreeflyAPI/QX_Protocol.c **** 	4. Assign parser callback functions for each client and server using QX_InitSrv() and QX_InitCli()
  33:..\..\FreeflyAPI/QX_Protocol.c **** 	5. Call the QX_Init() function at application startup.
  34:..\..\FreeflyAPI/QX_Protocol.c **** 	6. In a periodic loop (main, or control/comms task) call QX_StreamRxCharSM() for each port to rece
  35:..\..\FreeflyAPI/QX_Protocol.c **** 	7. Send any unsolicited messages such periodic current value messages (charting) and client read/w
  36:..\..\FreeflyAPI/QX_Protocol.c **** 
  37:..\..\FreeflyAPI/QX_Protocol.c **** 	There are 3 Main Message Types that can be sent via QX:
  38:..\..\FreeflyAPI/QX_Protocol.c **** 	CURRENT VALUE - Sent by server in response to read, write or periodically (charting). Recieved by 
  39:..\..\FreeflyAPI/QX_Protocol.c **** 	READ - Sent by client to request that a current value message be sent by server as a reply.
  40:..\..\FreeflyAPI/QX_Protocol.c **** 	WRITE (Absolute or Relative) - Sent by client to write data. Triggers a current value response by 
  41:..\..\FreeflyAPI/QX_Protocol.c **** 		
